      • getAmount

        public java.lang.String getAmount()
        Deprecated. As of v1.6.3 replaced by more general getElement(String). Please use getElement(PaymentData.AMOUNT) to obtain individual amount string.
        Amount in the smallest currency unit of given country (lipas, cents). If not recognized, the default is "".

        Example: If returned "1000" and currency is "EUR", actual amount is "10,00 EUR" If returned "123" and currency is "EUR", actual amount is "1,23 EUR" For currency EUR, minimum length of this value is 3 for the case like above.

        If returned "1000" and currency is "Ft (Forint), actual amount is "1000 Ft".
        If returned "1000" and currency is "Hrk", the case is like "EUR".
        If not sure how to interpret read amount, please use getParsedAmount() method.

        Returns:
        Amount to pay

      • isValid

        public boolean isValid()
        Flag denoting PhotoPay believes this is valid data to proceed to payment. If not really sure, the default is false. Use this value to adjust te UI accordingly. User should know if the recognized data is not 100% correct.
        Returns:
        true if the payment is valid, false otherwise.
